00:57:00.140 --> 00:57:01.440
So how does that differ?

00:57:01.440 --> 00:57:02.740
What is that like?

00:57:02.740 --> 00:57:04.040
&gt;&gt; Sheila Kay Adams: If there's
a young person in that crowd,

00:57:04.040 --> 00:57:05.340
I can guarantee you they'll be

00:57:05.340 --> 00:57:07.510
at my house spending the
night within six months.

00:57:07.510 --> 00:57:11.990
Because I'll bore in
on the young folks.

00:57:11.990 --> 00:57:14.210
Because you know, that's
where it is.

00:57:14.210 --> 00:57:17.070
That's what it's all about.

00:57:17.070 --> 00:57:23.530
It's about handing -- well nobody
said it better than Cecil Sharp.

00:57:23.530 --> 00:57:30.050
He said, "From birth we are
given this right to these songs.

00:57:30.050 --> 00:57:32.100
They belong to us."

