00:58:20.520 --> 00:58:26.850 position:56%
So tell us about what that was like.

00:58:26.850 --> 00:58:29.580
&gt;&gt; Sheila Kay Adams:
Well, as you know, Steve,

00:58:29.580 --> 00:58:34.940
my husband Jim committed
suicide in 2009 in March.

00:58:34.940 --> 00:58:41.920 position:56%
And I felt -- I didn't know if I was
going to make it through it or not.

00:58:41.920 --> 00:58:44.710
But the funniest thing happened.

00:58:44.710 --> 00:58:51.980
I started to remember these
songs that came from Granny.

00:58:51.980 --> 00:58:55.140
Because she would say, "You know,
laugh or cry, honey, sing a song.

00:58:55.140 --> 00:58:59.540
Laugh or cry, sing a song.

00:58:59.540 --> 00:59:00.840
That's what's going
to make you better.

00:59:00.840 --> 00:59:02.570
That's what's going to heal you."

00:59:02.570 --> 00:59:06.250
And so it was like I just
forgot about the here and now

00:59:06.250 --> 00:59:10.100
and I just leaned back, closed my
eyes and fell back into the arms

00:59:10.100 --> 00:59:16.160
of all those loving women
with all those songs.

00:59:16.160 --> 00:59:21.020
And Jeff Warner who's the son
of Frank and Ann Warner --

00:59:21.020 --> 00:59:24.100
