fine and nice and wonderful person.

00:59:34.590 --> 00:59:38.040
And he said, "Sheila, I'm
so sorry to hear about Jim.

00:59:38.040 --> 00:59:40.530
And I want to teach you a song."

00:59:40.530 --> 00:59:48.040
And I thought to myself, "I do not
believe that he just said he wants

00:59:48.040 --> 00:59:51.000
to teach me a song now, three
months after Jim's death."

00:59:51.000 --> 00:59:53.620
And he said, "No, this
is one, Sheila,

00:59:53.620 --> 00:59:56.490
I promise you've got
to learn this song."

00:59:56.490 --> 00:59:58.300
And he taught it to me.

00:59:58.300 --> 01:00:00.860
He sat down and I learned
it the old style.

01:00:00.860 --> 01:00:03.720
He'd sing it, I'd sing
it back to him.

01:00:03.720 --> 01:00:07.040
He'd sing it, I'd sing
it back to him.

01:00:07.040 --> 01:00:08.340
And that's how I learned it.

01:00:08.340 --> 01:00:12.840
And it was Her Bright Smile Haunts
Me Still, that was collected

01:00:12.840 --> 01:00:16.490
