in their background have.

01:01:22.860 --> 01:01:26.740
Which is you know, these tragedies
happen to us and then we realize

01:01:26.740 --> 01:01:29.630
that well, these tragedies
have happened before

01:01:29.630 --> 01:01:30.930
to generations of people.

01:01:30.930 --> 01:01:32.230
&gt;&gt; Sheila Kay Adams: For
thousands of years, that's right.

01:01:32.230 --> 01:01:33.530
&gt;&gt; Stephen Winnick: And
here it is in the songs

01:01:33.530 --> 01:01:35.200
that I already know and
that I already sing.

01:01:35.200 --> 01:01:36.500
&gt;&gt; Sheila Kay Adams: Yep.

01:01:36.500 --> 01:01:38.540
And you know, that's a gift
to be given those songs.

01:01:38.540 --> 01:01:42.000
And to be given that knowledge
that it ain't just you, honey.

01:01:42.000 --> 01:01:44.900
And somehow they made it through.

01:01:44.900 --> 01:01:46.790
&gt;&gt; Stephen Winnick:
Yeah, but then a couple

01:01:46.790 --> 01:01:48.380
